Availability.Beyond the Realms:
* [[Earth]], a planet where gunpowder functioned normally.<ref>{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2015)/How Earth Tech Functions in the Realms}}
* [[Krynn]] was known to lack gunpowder.{{Cite dragon/232/Sorcerous Six-Shooters|37}}
* [[Oerth]] was a planet that had gunpowder, but its local magic and physics rendered the substance inert.{{Cite dragon/232/Sorcerous Six-Shooters|36}}
* Beyond the [[Prime Material plane]], gunpowder could be found in the [[Domains of Dread]],<ref> such as [[Barovia]].<ref>

document_data.History:
Over time, Gond witnessed many mortals dying in explosions from experimenting with gunpowder.{{Cite web/theedverse/2021-07-08 - When Gunpowder Went Inert}}<ref><ref><ref><ref group="note" name="Years">The two dates presented are based on the sourcebooks ''[[Grand History of the Realms]]'' & [[Forgotten Realms Campaign Setting 2nd edition (revised)|''Forgotten Realms Campaign Setting'' (2nd edition)]], which both state that the Lantanese first tested bombards in [[1246 DR]] (later explained by Ed to be using gunpowder), and ''[[Forgotten Realms Campaign Set]]'', which is set between [[1356 DR|1356]]&mdash;[[1357 DR]] and states that gunpowder does not function on Toril.

During the [[Time of Troubles]], Gond in his mortal [[avatar]] form washed up on the shores of [[Lantan]]. To reward his followers there for sheltering him, he revealed to them the secret of how to make the alchemical substance smokepowder as an alternative to gunpowder, which due to precise proportions of a magical ingredient could circumvent his magics, allowing it to ignite and explode. He also revealed to them how to create firearms utilizing the substance that were safe and reasonably accurate.

Following the [[Spellplague]], while Gond was in a weakened state and the nation of Lantan was in [[Abeir|another world]], the clergy of [[Kossuth]] tried to spread a claim that gunpowder's inert state on Toril was the doing of their god.{{Cite web/theedverse/2019-05-30 - How Gunpowder Works in the Forgotten Realms}}
